				<td colspan="2"><span>Heya All, new Bard here. Expect lots of pointless newb questions from me. 
<br />

<br />
By no means new to EQ, but over the time I have been playing I would always be switching classes, never able to decide which was best for me. 
<br />

<br />
One of our main Bards in the guild told me I should play a Bard, as I like a bit of everything... 
<br />

<br />
I needed a toon that could solo and group well, one who could get into odd spots and slip away undetected. 
<br />

<br />
Tried a lot of toons - but only had played a Bard to level 10.. I kept telling my guildie I really don't think I'd like a Bard - but, alas - I started another one. So far, he's been great fun, maybe if I can get that kiting down I will really stick to this class<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
We will see!
<br />

<br />
Oh - speaking of newb questions.. I have the basics of instrument switching down - say, if you wanna twist Selos and Heal - switching the Lute and Drum back and forth.. Question is... in order to get the benefit of the instrutment, does it have to be equipped at the second you start playing the song, or just by the time the spell bar finishes it's casting? In other words - if I start casting Selos and during the cast time, move the lute out and put the drum in place, will I get the added speed from the percussion instrument?</span></td>
