				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, actually I wanted to play on FV for a long time - I made a Chanter there a long time ago, but ended up staying on Cazic-Thule - long Story. I've jumped around a little too much in this game, hehe.
<br />

<br />
If it wasn't for all the gear I got, I'd consider it, I kinda like the RP server. It's just hard to give up the Fungi and all.. hehe
<br />

<br />
After reading a couple threads, I'm glad I came here alright - even when I wasn't playing a Bard, I was always impressed by EQdiva's web site - best class site of any in EQ, IMO. 
<br />

<br />
I think the best thing I've read this morning was some of the threds on kiting, and how it can make a Bard look like a real a$$ - and that is SO true. I've ran into a couple, and they really stick out like sore thumbs, sometimes you gotta bite your lip too.. Overall, I haven't had any more problems with Bards than I have had with Stupid clerics tho (insert whatever class). My point in coming here is so I don't play a &quot;dork&quot; Bard - considering the skills of this class, it's easy to see why they can be a cause of problems in the right situation. Of course, it's the player not that class. I'm not in a major hurry to level or anything really. 
<br />

<br />
That's pretty sweet, thanks for the info, that gives me a bit more room to swap them, it would be rather tricky to swtich them out right before casting, glad it works that way.</span></td>
