				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New Bard<a name="72766"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 31 05 2:14 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I like the prospect of swarm kiting most of all - although I would have liked to try the large DoT kites too.. 
<br />

<br />
I do see the taunt effect of the chants, even in PC last night I could grab mobs off of casters with the Chants, worked rather well. 
<br />

<br />
Luckily, I didn't come to play the class for one reason - quite the contrary. I'm tired of getting stuck in a narrow line in EQ. I like versatility, but I also like the ability to do a few things *very* well. I have had plenty of experience charm soloing with a chanter, and just don't care for it.. See along with my two core requirements - class must be able to group and solo - I have one other requirement... Ability to get the h*ll out of dodge, shoudl things get goofed. I don't mind a risk at all, but I like to have my escape, and will plan ahead of time to do my best to insure I have one. 
<br />

<br />
This took a lot of classes out of the mix. Mages don't have a quick escape, Necro's are real good in groups (that's debatable, maybe, but put LFG up, see how many tells you get, hehe). Enchanters can solo (slowly), have a quick escape (mez/root/gate) and are good in groups, but they kill kinda slow and you don't see the real good solo power until DC.. 
<br />

<br />
So anyway, without rationalizing every class in the game here, I finally came to the conclusion that only 4 classes had what I wanted. Druid's are ok I guess - just not othe class for me, I tried one, just don't care for root/cook soloing most of the time. Shammy was a fair soloer, good in groups, and could at least root and gate if all else failed. Enchanter was good, but gosh I hate paper armor, and finally - the Bard. 
<br />

<br />
Well, the Bard's no tank, I understand that (not counting 1-25, those levels are purely dependant on gear, not skill and not counting Time+ geared Bards tanking in PoV, but that's another issue.. heh) but at least the Bard has a decent amount of armor, can solo well, and is great in a group. 
<br />

<br />
I'm no huge fan of pulling... with FD and such, but Lull pulling I can handle ok, mostly.
<br />

<br />
I fully expect Sony to keep changing things and all, which is my final reason for playing a Bard. They are adaptable, I think they are able to adjust to changes fairly well. 
<br />

<br />
Even with Sony's latest nerf, there are still more than one viable options for good XP soloing. Well, for now.. 
<br />

<br />
With server populations down so far, messing with soloing is probably the very worst thing they can do. 
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
