				<td colspan="2"><span>How does that go again... Oh ya, &quot;Once you go bard, you never go back.&quot;
<br />

<br />
To true, at least for me.  The keys for me were Mezz, lull, and Selos... or maybe Selos should be first.  You get all of those in the first few levels, and only ADD things (group haste, charm, more group buffs/resists, chants, etc) from there till the late 50's.  Late 50's and early 60's you effectively loose a lot of your abilities, then regain them in the mid 60's.
<br />

<br />
Once you get Fading Memories @ 63, there are very few places you can't get into alone... if you're like me, I carry instant gate potions, gate potions, and OT Hammer all to get myself OUT of some of the places I've arrived... and make sure to keep a necro or SK as a friend. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" />
<br />

